comments: Avdija (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Randle (NYK) in the post.
Kuzma (WAS) is in the paint for around three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Randle (NYK) is deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Burks (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position on Holiday (WAS) during the drive.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Holiday (WAS) loses control of the ball on his gather and attempted pass at the end of his drive. He is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and the Knicks are correctly awarded possession.
Kuzma (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive.
After the made basket, Robinson (NYK) grabs the ball with two hands and redirects it away from the inbounder. A delay of game violation should be called.
Randle (NYK) legally contests Kuzma's (WAS) jump shot attempt and any contact with Kuzma's arm after the release is deemed incidental.
Dinwiddie (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive. Dinwiddie makes clean ball contact on his steal attempt at the end of the drive.

Avdija (WAS) makes contact with Burks' (NYK) arm, which affects his shot near the rim. Burks receives the pass outside of and ends his play inside the lower defensive box when Avdija makes contact with his arm, and a shooting foul is correctly assessed.
Robinson (NYK) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Walker (NYK) and DInwiddie (WAS) pursue the loose ball and incidental contact occurs as they come together during the rebound.
Walker (NYK) commits a take foul on Avdija (WAS).
During the screen, Burks (NYK) and Dinwiddie (WAS) mutually engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Robinson (NYK) moves into and makes contact with DInwiddie's (WAS) body, which affects his SQBR on the perimeter.
Dinwiddie (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position on Walker (NYK) at the end of the drive.  He places a forearm at his side without extending it and the contact is incidental.
Gafford (WAS) maintains his defensive path alongside of Walker (NYK) and absorbs the marginal contact initiated by Walker on his driving shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) and DInwiddie (WAS) pursue the loose ball and any contact as they come together is deemed incidental during the rebound.
Holiday (WAS) legally contests Fournier's (NYK) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Burks (NYK) brings his arm down and makes contact with Gafford's (WAS) shoulder, which dislodges him during the rebound.
Avdija (WAS) makes contact with Randle's (NYK) wrist, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Toppin (NYK) commits a take foul on Kispert (WAS).
Toppin (NYK) commits a take foul on Kuzma (WAS).
